[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aaron Heremaia: Widnes Vikings hooker signs new deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Widnes Vikings hooker Aaron Heremaia has signed a new one-year contract extension until 2017.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 33-year-old one-time New Zealand international joined the Vikings at the start of 2015 from Hull FC and featured in every single game.
Heremaia spent three seasons in Super League with the Black and Whites after joining them from NRL side New Zealand Warriors.
"I'm really enjoying my time here and I'm very happy to stay," he said.
"It's a very professional set-up here and it was an easy decision to commit for another year."
